  "title": "The NIMH Healthy Research Volunteer Dataset",
  "description": "The NIMH Healthy Research Volunteer Dataset is a comprehensive neuroimaging and clinical characterization study of 1,859 healthy adults. The dataset includes structural and functional MRI, diffusion tensor imaging, magnetoencephalography, cognitive assessments, psychiatric evaluations, and biospecimens. This resource enables investigations into normal cognition, mood regulation, and brain function across a deeply phenotyped healthy population.",
  "methods_description": "Data collection includes clinical interviews (SCID-5), cognitive testing (KBIT-2, NIH Toolbox), psychiatric assessments (DSM-5 measures, WHODAS 2.0), and neuroimaging. MRI protocol includes T1, T2, FLAIR, pCASL, DTI, and resting-state fMRI acquisitions. MEG battery comprises resting-state, task-based, and empty room recordings. Biological measures include blood pressure, laboratory panels, and banked blood samples for genetic analysis.",
